The paper focuses on creating an efficient object detection network for an AI-powered assistant for object localization for the visually impaired, which falls under the computer vision (cs.CV) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories. The study also involves micro-architecture design exploration to optimize the network's performance, which relates to machine learning (cs.LG) and robotics (cs.RO) sub-categories. Finally, the paper aims to enable assistive devices for individuals with visual impairment, which falls under the human-computer interaction (cs.HC) sub-category.
